        <updateDate>2003-08-27T19:56:43Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Secure Annuity Income for Life Act of 2003 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exclude from gross income a percentage of lifetime annuity payments from a qualified trust to a qualified distributee. Provides for recapture and taxation of payments that are modified (other than by death or disability) so as to not qualify as lifetime annuity payments.</p> <p>Applies such exclusion to: (1) section 403(a) plans (employee annuities); (2) section 403(b) plans (public schools and certain tax exempt organizations); (3) section 408 plans (individual retirement accounts); and (4) section 457 plans (deferred compensation plans for State and local governments and tax-exempt organizations). </p> <p>Defines: (1) &quot;lifetime annuity payment&quot;; and (2) &quot;qualified distributee.&quot;</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
